citeinfo.title: England 1:10 000, Walsall, BB 17h. (1942)

pubinfo.publish: Germany. Generalstab des Heeres, Abteilung fuer Kriegskarten- und Vermessungswesen

citeinfo.othercit: Alternate title: Stadtplan von Leeds mit militaergeographischen Eintragungen. Grossblatt 6, Blattbereich 9r. Relief shown by 25 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. Gauss-Krueger grid. Legend is in English and German. With a list of abbreviations. Source: Ordnance Survey 1:10,560. Accompanied by 66p. booklet: "Militaergeographische Einzelangaben ueber England; Objektbilder zu den militaergeographischen Objektkarten 1:250 000 und 1:10 000 der Mappe 6 Nord-Midlands"; of photographs and drawings of important military objectives, bridges, factories, etc. (sites are located on map).

descript.abstract: This is a map of the city of Walsall, England, shown at a 1:10,000. The map was created for use by German War and Navy Department agencies during World War II.
descript.purpose: The purpose is to view the map in digital format.

idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows 2000 Version 5.0 (Build 2195) Service Pack 4; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.0.0.535

procstep.procdesc: This map was scanned with a Chroma Tx 40 Plus Wide Format color scanner and WIDEimage 2.8 software at 400 DPI in 24-bit color. The image was then reduced to 256 colors and saved in a TIFF file format. Later the TIFF image was compressed by the Mapping Science GeoJP2 software version 1.04.02. The compression ratio was 10:1.
